      Executes the command using the provided data
      Parameters:
      message - the message and relevant data that triggered the command to run
      Returns:
      The result of executing the command. If the command would like to persist, it should return AbstractCommand.ContinuePersistingCommandResponse.PASS or make a new one with a message to send to the bois in discord

    • runOnServerArrival

      public AbstractCommand.AbstractCommandResponse runOnServerArrival​(AbstractCommand.AbstractCommandData message)
      Different from run(frc.discordslackbot.commands.AbstractCommand.AbstractCommandData), should only ever be redefined by multitick commands and should only contain initial processing required before the command goes stale while waiting to persist. Such reasons may include rejecting a command based on settings, acknowledging a command is valid,
      Parameters:
      message - the data from the message that caused the message
      Returns:
      A response in accordance with the return of run(AbstractCommandData)

    • extractData

      public AbstractCommand.AbstractCommandData extractData​(net.dv8tion.jda.api.events.message.MessageReceivedEvent message)
